entries.title: Dell to lay off 6,650 workers, or 5% of its workforce
entries.description: Dell on Monday announced plans to lay off more than 6,650 employees, or about 5% of its workforce.

entries.title: Retailers in China enact rare price cuts for Apple's high-end iPhone 14 line
entries.description: Price cuts to Apple's iPhone 14 Pro and Pro Max in China come amid a smartphone demand slump in the world's second-largest economy.

entries.title: A prominent UK cybersecurity stock is under attack from short sellers. Here's what you need to know
entries.description: Cybersecurity firm Darktrace was targeted in a short seller report from New York-based asset manager Quintessential Capital Management.

entries.title: Soccer's Premier League claims Manchester City breached financial rules
entries.description: The club will face a commission over alleged rule breaking between 2009 and 2016 regarding financial reporting on revenue and manager and player remuneration.

entries.title: Former UK PM Liz Truss is blaming the left-wing 'economic establishment' for ousting her
entries.description: Former U.K. Prime Minister Liz Truss is blaming a "powerful economic establishment" for bringing her chaotic 44-day tenure to an end last year.

entries.title: Second earthquake rocks Turkey and Syria as death toll from first quake reaches 1,300
entries.description: A second earthquake struck Turkey and Syria on Monday, after the death toll from a first quake rose near 1,300.

entries.title: China urges calm after U.S. shoots down suspected spy balloon
entries.description: China's Ministry of Foreign Affairs spokesperson Mao Ning urged both sides to remain calm after the U.S. said it shot down what it called a Chinese spy balloon.

entries.title: London’s rental market is in crisis. Here’s why and how renters are struggling
entries.description: High demand and low supply have led to soaring prices and a rental market crisis in London.

entries.title: From Nike to Nutella: Company names you have probably been mispronouncing your whole life
entries.description: Global company names often get Americanized or Anglicized to the point where they're unrecognizable.

entries.title: Adani rout deepens despite soothing words from India's government and billionaires
entries.description: Most Adani Group companies shed market cap on Monday, as the feud between the conglomerate and a short seller firm further deepened.

entries.title: U.S.-China relations just got more fragile
entries.description: U.S.-China relations look increasingly fragile, analysts say, after a now-downed Chinese balloon forced the U.S. Secretary of State to postpone a Beijing trip.

entries.title: Huawei turns to patents for a lifeline — including those in the U.S.
entries.description: Chinese telecommunications giant Huawei is turning to patents for a lifeline while it tests a path forward in advanced chip technology.

entries.title: This college dropout sold his first company for six figures at 21. Here's his recipe for success
entries.description: Kevin Kim's new startup Stadium Live has a star-studded list of investors, including NBA star Kevin Durant and World Cup champion Blaise Matuidi.

entries.title: January's U.S. jobs reports was stunningly good
entries.description: January’s U.S. jobs report is so stunningly good that it looks bad for investors hoping for an interest rate pause.
